     &lt;allow-origin&gt;*://*.jmx4perl.org&lt;/allow-origin&gt;

     &lt;!-- Check for the proper origin on the server side, too --&gt;
     &lt;strict-checking/&gt;
    &lt;/cors&gt;

For more details please refer [4.1.5. Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) restrictions][1]


  [1]: https://jolokia.org/reference/html/security.html

 Jolokia&#39;s  default setting will block all CORS
   &lt;restrict&gt;
    
        &lt;cors&gt;
            &lt;!-- Allow cross origin access from localhost ... --&gt;
            &lt;allow-origin&gt;*://localhost*&lt;/allow-origin&gt;
    
    
            &lt;!-- Options from this point on are auto-generated by Create.java from the Artemis CLI --&gt;
            &lt;!-- Check for the proper origin on the server side, too --&gt;
            &lt;strict-checking/&gt;
        &lt;/cors&gt;
    
    &lt;/restrict&gt;

Just remove the  `&lt;strict-checking/&gt;` tag from the above default configuration in `jolokia-access.xml`

